hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
The staff at this hotel were super friendly and always helpful. My cell phone was having issues when we arrived and one of the young men at the front desk was able to fix the issue. The location was very good, close to the metro that took us anywhere we wanted to go in Paris without issue.
The breakfast was really good as well. Thank you for a great experience.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
This is a pretty basic hotel but I have to give it 5 stars due mainly to the staff. The front desk staff were so welcoming and made us feel instantly at ease. We were a bit early and they facilitated an early check in for us and were constantly helpful throughout our stay.

The housekeeping staff were equally great!

Rooms were comfortable and there was coffee and tea making facilities as well as free water and little snacks which were appreciated. Hotel is situated in the heart of the 8th arrondissement and everything was sighing easy reach.

I would definitely return to this hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I was here for a congress. My room was large and clean, with all modern comforts. The staff was friendly and helpful. the breakfast war rich and was to my satisfaction. the congress room was well organised . the prices are a bit high

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
This hotel is always on the top of my list when visiting Paris, its the perfect location, near all the great attractions and designers shopping district.

The staff are always very friendly, Araci front desk manager, always makes sure I am well looked after, the lady in the breakfast area was absolutely delightful and such a friendly personality to see in the morning

The hotel exterior, front desk, lobby area and breakfast area have recently been renovated and it looks amazing. The owner does a super job and keeping the hotel in a great standard, which makes the value for your money worth the stay

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Top location. Easy access to mayor highlights of Paris. Good access with public transport. Very friendly professional staff. Room large enough for 3 adults. Good breakfast buffet with nice offer. Hotel to return to. Up to the IHG member standards

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Holiday Inn bills this as a four star hotel. They must be joking. I've stayed in student hostels that were better: this hotel features small, dank, shabby rooms right off a busy but charmless street. I wasn't expecting luxury, but for nearly 500 euros a night I don't think it's unreasonable to expect a fresh, clean, quiet place to stay. Avoid this one. AND DO NOT BELIEVE THE PHOTOS POSTED BY THE HOTEL! They are eithet using really old photos or an industrial strength instagram filter. AVOID!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This is a classic boutique feeling European hotel. The rooms are very small but we found space for all our clothes and items for the week and tucked our suitcases out of the way. It's a relatively quiet area at night. The water pressure and water temp was amazing (one thing I struggle with at European hotels a lot!). Great area to get where you need to go, Paris is huge so you end up taking uber/metro/bus no matter where you stay. There's a wonderful chocolate shop and a couple of cafes just around the corner but the star is the tiny market across the street that has just about anything you would need. Please remember this is a 4 star hotel not 5 star. If you want a 5 star hotel, go pay 5 star prices. The front desk staff was amazing, I listened to one speak 3 different languages helping all of the guests within about 5 minutes. We had a great week ans would definitely return to this hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Good business htel. Excellent to perfect location on rive droite, triangle dor, close to the Champs Elyses, Elysee palace, the luxury shopping avenues .. kind and efficient staff. Rooms rather small and aged. Decent value for money considering the area.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
UnFriendy and more unhelpful staff
Be more intuitive to see a hot and sweating guest checking in and offer a glass of water
Notify guests that the name holiday inn Champs-lyses, does not mean its close to the Champs-lyses.
Its rather a business area with very little restaurants
Rooms are small with no view and no space

The room was identified as a executive room but was nothing like that. Our second room was a normal room and was much better. We asked to be moved and each room was worst than the previous so we just resorted to accepting the below par room as best of the worst.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: First time in Paris and the hotel definitely made it more memorable. Excellent front desk, many thanks to Steve and to the wonderfull lady who check us out seamlessly and called a taxi for us. Perfect location for the the sights to see. You can walk to the Eiffel Tower and the Sacre Coeur Basilica. Champs Elysee is just a 12 minute walk. Breakfast was great. Special thanks to Michael who gave us excellent service. Definitely will come back.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
I lived in Paris for four month with my girlfriend and we know Paris very well - therefor I can say, that the location of this hotel is just perfect! You can easily walk to every Landmark.
The room was not only clean and well furnished but also super Good sized and comfortable.
Definitely a recommendation!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Mistakes can happen, things can get forgotten- the question stays how the hotel is dealing with it.
In this hotel was the reaction miserable.
We had no duvet so we got one from the reception but no cover for it. Because the housekeeping crew was already off from work.
So we needed to carry the duvet without a cover by ourselves upstairs. - NOWAY 4 STAR HOTEL!

The next day nobody cares about it and when i told the reception manager what happened she was not professional at all and assumed me i would lie!
It was very unhygienic to sleep there. .

The bed was very uncomfortable, you can feel the feathers very good on your back.

And the towels are very old, they should be replaced

So a advice from me to the hotel : when you want to be professional you should fire the one with the ruff and the women who is reception manager.
The rest was fine but those two made the stay very uncomfortable.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Everything was excellent,but most of all mr mamadou was amazing and willing to help us in every demand!The hotel was near the center of the city and it also had a variety choices for breakfast.Finally the room was very clean and well decorated

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
I stayed here for work because I wanted a nice, safe, full-service hotel. I am a long-term IHG customer. When I arrived from the airport, I saw it was in a rather seedy area, and there was only one staff member on duty. (another one turned up a bit later but that may have just been a replacement). There was no restaurant. I went to see my room and it was in an internal 'well' with no external view. As I am claustrophobic this was no good. The elevator was tiny and old-fashioned and lights only came on in the tiny, drab landing when you stepped out of the elevator. I found it quite scary.
There was nobody to show me to a better room so I decided to move to another hotel, as I just did not feel safe in this hotel (I was travelling alone). Luckily I found another one on the web with vacancies, which on arrival proved to be bright, well-staffed and in a nice area. The staff at the Holiday Inn did book a taxi for me.
I arrived early evening. I had changed my travel plans due to a family emergency, and my original plan would have had me arriving very late at night from a flight from Australia. I don't know what I would have done under these circumstances.
The Holiday Inn was outrageously expensive, and I was booked for three nights. I then had to pay again at the better hotel. I asked the Holiday Inn for a refund and they refused, although I had not used any service st all. I then tried IHG (the chain), as I am a long-term customer, but they also refused. I was astonished. Holiday Inn will certainly never be my first choice again, anywhere in the world.
This hotel is definitely not for women travelling alone.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The front desk staff at the hotel were exceptional and friendly . They were extremely helpful even though I asked them question after question. Rooms were clean and really a great size. Location was excellent. Just a few minutes from the Champs Elysee as well as Haussmann. Great service. Really appreciated the hospitality from the front desk staff.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Location is great, staff is really nice, WiFi was fast and the cleaning was ON TOP! I dont think Ive ever stayed in a cleaner room. Every day it was freshened up.

Just a note, the room we stayed in had minor issues like the door to the bathroom wouldnt really shut all the way.

Overall, we were super impressed! Thanks for the hospitality.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
In short, simple and elegant! What really makes this place a special and a preferred one for me in Paris is not only its central location, but the the amazing and friendly staff .. very helpful, professional and will never let you down.
Special thanks to my friend Steeve and his colleagues Emile and Arasi

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Just got back from Paris and unlike my other reviews that I was super late on posting, I wanted to make sure I posted this review. The location was easy to get to, but you need to be the walking type. You can always Uber to and from, but it's more fun to walk to and from Champs Elysees to the hotel.It's a quieter walk, but after a noisy day of touristy activities, you'll appreciate it. BUT: The reason I wanted to post this right away - is the staff. YES. They were amazing! Starting with the male at the front desk when we arrived, he was doing his best and was very polite, in spite of fighting a mean cold. Also, there was lovely yound lady that was very attentive during our breakfast the next morning. We checked out, but needed to return to pick up our things after a day of sightseeing, and when we returned, the last person we interacted with was a young lady, Siriny R., who was professional and kind, and very helpful in responding to our many questions. She was just delightful! I'd stay here again.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I thought I booked in a 4 star hotel, in a nice street... Exact opposite!! The hotel is a 3 star Max, if you see the pics on booking. Com you'd love it but when you get there you will be shocked! Couldn't move in the room it was tiny, old furniture very small toilet horrible elevator, no porter no help whatsoever no room service no attention to details, Noone replenished the coffee tray for 3 days... To make a long story short I wouldn't stay there again...

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
This Holiday Inn is well located to get around Paris - lots to see close by and a couple of minutes away from the Metro. Its not cheap; and it is basically just somewhere to sleep. Breakfast is a ridiculous 18 each - on top of steep nightly rates. But this is central Paris.

Theres loads of good places to eat on the doorstep - which makes up for a really poor bar and no restaurant.

Finally, hats off to the staff - all were really good and friendly...

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This hotel is located in a fairly quiet part of Paris and is within walking distance to the famed Champs lyses. The staff were helpful and the rooms comfortable however the fold out sofa bed that my children had to sleep on was extremely uncomfortable, the mattress was so thin, springs could be felt every time they moved. The main king bed though was very comfortable. The breakfast was adequate and the hotel was very clean.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Friendly staff, decent breakfast selection and conveniently located next to a metro station and small supermarket. The rooms are small, but that is to be expected in Paris. Bathroom and shower were a good size. Air conditioning worked well.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I went to Paris on 07/09/2019 and stayed at Holiday Inn Paris Elysees. I must say, that, I was so pleased to be in that hotel. I was greeted by Mr. Steeve at the reception and I must say he was absolutely brilliant in checking me in and subsequently guiding me to the right place to visit the monuments. Throughout my stay he was very helpful and humble. I must also mention Mr. Emile at the reception during nights. He was exceptional as well, whether it was ordering food or serving drinks. The hotel was very good, clean and had very good breakfast. The location was fantastic and safe with the Official Residence of the President being around. The room was nice but the bathroom was very big. I would recommend this hotel to every one because I am going to stay there again.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
After checking out of another hotel nearby, just TRYING to find a new hotel to stay in that was clean, we were so pleasantly surprised at what a delight this hotel is. It's a far cry from the Holiday Inn properties we have stayed in while traveling through the US!

The rooms are large, with comfortable US King sized beds. I had 2 amazing nights sleep here, and after leaving the other (disgusting) property, felt like I had found the Taj Mahal! The bathrooms are large, clean and they have AMAZING water pressure! If you get a room with a rain shower, all the better! Some have tubs, which are also nice.

The property itself is really clean. They offer "team time" in the lobby every day, with tea, coffee and assorted pastries. They also have jars of sweets out all day long, along with mint flavored water. They do offer breakfast, for 18 euro, but we didn't try it. The air conditioner is cooling after a warm day outside, but if you want to crack open the windows you can ABSOLUTELY let some fresh air in!

The hotel is perfectly situated near the Champs-Elysees, the Eiffel Tower, the Arc de Triomphe, and other sites to see throughout Paris.

The staff is truly amazing. Kind, easy to speak to, and helpful! Steeve at the front desk was a standout & should be commended for his customer service!

We would definitely stay here again!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I stayed here.for 6 nights, the hotel location is quite nice with a 1 min walk metro station and walking distance from most shopping areas . The stuff are so friendly specifically the reception team . All of them are friendly and helpful. Breakfast is fine but can have more options as live omelette station . The only bad thing was the elevators were so slow and take ages to reach with no sound proof rooms

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: We stayed as a family of four the last week of July. We had adjoining rooms on the first floor. This was very nice as we have two teenage girls who need their own bathroom. We are IHG members and this suite was for Members. The included breakfast was very good. It is a small hotel and it did not seem to be a lot of people there when we were there. It was in close proximity to the champs d elysees. We walked and used Uber for our three night star. We did not use the public transportation but it was close to hotel. We enjoyed this hotel and would return. There were two very good restaurants near the hotel, one was JJ and the other La Traboule. Steeve at the front desk was extremely helpful. He gave us directions and helped us avoid the crowds the day the tour de France came into Paris. He told us how to walk up to the arc de triomphe to watch the end of the race and avoid the crowds on the champs d elysees. Would highly recommend as pretty centrally located.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: From the moment we walked in the staff what helpful. We arrived before the room was ready so they checked our bags, gave us directions and pointed us to their complementary afternoon snacks. The rooms were nice and the bathrooms amazing. Every time we past the front desk we were greeted with smiles. The transportation we thought we had to the airport didn't have us confirmed when we checked the night before. So, at about 1am I went to the desk and asked for help. The gentleman told me not to worry about it. He said go to bed and I'll have the taxi for you in the morning. He took care of it and a taxi arrived at the requested time. I may not make it back to Paris but if I do this is where I'll be staying.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Stayed for 2 nights with friends.
From the welcome on arrival to the farewell on departure, it was an enjoyable stay.
The hotel is a few hundred meters from a metro station so really easy to get to/from.
The receptionists were friendly and helpful, as we arrived early, they checked us in and looked after our luggage so we could go and see the sights.
In the evening, when we returned, our room was ready and we were given the key - the room was small but functional and the only thing missing was a bedside table to place things on.
Breakfast was a buffet but had everything we needed - if we wanted eggs, we could have had them cooked fresh.
We had a nightcap when we got back and the receptionist doubled up as the barman - did a great job in serving us all.
We expected a lot less of the hotel than they delivered and I would happily recommend it and will probably stay there again when next in Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Our short stay at this little hotel was most enjoyable. I can't say enough about the courteous, accommodating front desk staff. We arrived early, and they stored our bags while offering tea, and snacks in the little bistro area. We asked and received wonderful recommendations of cafes in the area, as well as directions, etc. The hotel is conveniently located near the Champs Elysses with it's wonderful shopping and people-watching, as well as the Arc d"Triumphe. Parking is difficult, but I wouldn't recommend a car in Paris, anyway.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
While we were staying Steeve, Araci and Siriny were at the desk. They were outstanding. They made sure we felt as close to being at home as possible. Service overall was great from the breakfast and host in the morning, to tea time in the afternoon and cocktails before dinner.
The location is excellent. Walking distance to the Champs Eleysee and the Metro is one block that gets you anywhere in Paris. We took the RER B from CDG and then Metro to Miromesnil.
Nice restaurants nearby too.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We stayed at this hotel for a week recently. It was convenient for us to walk to many attractions in Paris or to hop on the metro.  The room size was typical European but very clean with a large bed, desk and a nice size bathroom.  

What made this hotel outstanding was Steeve Bazot at the front desk. This young man was pleasant and always helpful with directions, restaurants, and attractions.  He welcomed us back from our excursions and was truly interested in what we thought about them. Steeve made our stay at this Holiday Inn very pleasant.  A professional representative that serves this hotel exceptionally well.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: One of the finest, good value for money hotel we could find for our stay in Paris. It's little old property but staff is excellent, very cooperative and the Nespresso coffee machine and cookies in the room was a bonus. Breakfast is excellent and staff was always attentive and ready to help. All of us travelling were vegetarians and they took extra care of the same. Even while checking out, they could find taxi for us at a much cheaper price than UBER. Very close to metro station and so very easy to travel in Paris by metro if you are staying here. Just buy Zone 1-2 tickets in metro and you are ready to go. Very close to both the palaces.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Stayed here for four nights and found this hotel to have good location and really friendly staff. Bedroom is usual small Parisian size but bed very comfortable. WiFi was good and encountered no problems. Breakfast was 18 euro and was worth it as it had options of hot and cold food. Overall as good as you might get in Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: We used IHG points. IHG does minimum for its faithful customers than any of the international chains. When you use points, you cannot bloom any of t he package offerings (room plus parking or room plus breakfast) plus you will always get the lowest class room with no chance of the upgrade, even for Platinum plus ambassador. They make s big deal out of points until you use them. Our room literally had 12 inches surrounding the bed. When walking to the bathroom, my wife had to get on the bed and pull feet up so I could pass. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Location is good and 3 minutes to metro. Breakfast substantially overpriced and if you want a cup of coffee, you will part with 5 euros. But 4 reasonable breakfast options nearby. Particularly glad I did not pay real money. This is not the first time i have found IHG not honoring its Platinum Ambassador members.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We stayed for 2 nights, 23rd to 25th February. First impressions were good, clean reception area and very welcoming receptionist.
The hotel is a small boutique style, what you would expect from a property in Paris.
We had booked the Executive King room which had a lovely french door style window in the bedroom area and the en suite. It was plenty big enough for what we needed. Room was clean with small mini bar (quite pricey), tea and coffee making facilities and safe. We personally didnt have any issues with the free WiFi.
Breakfast had a good selection including a small area with a few cooked items, fruit, cereals, breads and pastries.
All staff that we interacted with were very friendly but I must stay the hospitality we received from Steeve was second to none. He is an asset to this hotel, nothing was too much trouble at all. He even gave me his phone to choose some music to listen to through the speakers in the bar whilst we were having a drink!
The location was good, about 15 mins walk from the Champs-Elyses. Would recommend the Big Bus tour to see the sights its hop on hop off. You can buy tickets for this at the hotel reception.
I would definitely return to this hotel if I visit Paris again!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This was a good option for a brief business trip, with easy access to the metro and walking distance to good eats, shopping, and other tourist areas. The lobby is nice and the staff are very pleasant. Rooms are small, which is not surprising, so this would not be ideal if you will be spending a lot of time in your room. Breakfast is expensive, but there are great bakery and cafe options just down the street.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Overall had a great stay at the Hotel and would stay again

Pros:
- Very Helpful/friendly staff
- Location was perfect... Close to a metro station and tourist attractions (Even had a little shop outside open until 2AM)
- Bed was comfy and the room was cleaned well
- Complimentary Tea Time (Croissants/Tea/Coffee) from 11AM-3PM

Cons:
- Near a busy road, and at times with the police sirens it was noisy but overall bearable
- Room was very small. Not much space to move around and for luggage... Would be problematic for longer stays
- Wifi was terrible. Could just about stream Netflix and sometimes would take 5 minutes plus to load a video
- Air Con was broken in our room... Was not a major problem during the time of stay

Overall would rate 3.5 stars and would stay again. But be aware of the issues outlined above.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: From the unexpected upgrade to the extended checkout time, this stay was a good one. Here for business and a late flight out, being able to stay at the room longer was great. Super friendly (and helpful) front desk staff, comfortable room that was well appointed And a location that is super... I will not only recommend this Holiday Inn to others but also will consider it for my future stays in Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: As an Spire Elite member I was offered 1 drink from the mini bar (normally SE members get 2 when travelling with partners). The minibar had 1 can of Coke and 1 can of beer - all very warm due to fridge being faulty. Other than this negative, the hotel is in a good location. Smaller than your average HI. A nice gesture is that from 11am there is free coffee and pastries in the lobby. Small supermarket outside great for late night purchases. Would I stay again - yes :)

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Its the best hotel in Paris.
Very good location that help you go walking to Champs Elysees.

I was lucky to reserve the rooms with STEVE, He is one of the best reception in the world.

Its highly recommended to make the check in on the afternoon, during the time of his work, he will make every thing very easy to you.

Its clean hotel, nice people.

I wish to be in this hotel one more time.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Rooms are tiny,clean, coffee machine,Iron board, safety box, free wifi and comfortable bed. breakfast was good and delicious. In the afternoon hotel provide free coffee, tea and croissant in the lobby.Several restaurants nearby . Ten to fifteen minutes walk to Champs-Elyses street and to Lafayette gallery. Friendly staff and special thanks to Ms.Tricia and Michael were very helpful .

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I had a problem with the laundry service and they support me all the time, even they made a reimbursement for my problem. Great service!, the Hotel is very good located and food is nice. Good option if you want to stay in Champs Elysees area.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Location was brilliant but the rest was below the average.
Room was smelling terribly, not clean, not hygene.
Service was below the average, team was average.
It was one of the worst holiday inn i ever stayed.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
It was my first time to use Holiday Inn Elysee, but after interacting with Gaelle, I'll make sure it is my destination in Paris. She is really great person to deal with and knows how customers are to be treated, I'm looking forward to my next visit already.

Thank you Gaelle & Team

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
This hotel falls far below the standards I would expect from a full-service Holiday Inn. It was just about adequate for my two-night stay. I'm glad I wasn't staying any longer.

On the positive side, the location is good: walking distance from the Champs Elyses and the Seine (Pont Alexandre III). There is a metro station at the end of the street and several cafs and bars nearby. My room was clean, the bed comfortable and the wi-fi acceptable. The staff were efficient and reasonably polite, although not particularly friendly or welcoming.

The biggest problem was noise. The hotel stands at a junction of two busy roads, with car horns tooting and motorbikes roaring all day and late into the night. The streets are narrow with high buildings on all sides, so the noise echoes upwards, making sleep difficult. There was also quite lot of internal noise, and this was not helped by the loud pop music blaring out in the public rooms (I couldn't hear this in my second-floor room).

The other big problem was the lack of space. My room was small to start with. With a king-sized bed in place, there was almost no room at all to move around or put things down. It was almost impossible to unpack my bags and nowhere to put my clothes, most of which ended up on the floor. There was one tiny cupboard, but I couldn't open its door without having to move furniture around. Even getting out of bed was difficult without crashing into the TV. The bathroom was also very cramped.

And this was with a single-person occupancy. Heaven knows how a couple would have managed in that tiny space.

The stupid thing is that the room would have been adequate if it had a normal-sized bed. As it was, the enormous king-side bed took up most of the space. A smaller bed with more room to move and store things would have been more sensible.

I chose not to take the breakfast. After a glance at the unappealing choices on offer, I could see no way that it justified the price of 18. Fortunately, I found a nice boulangerie on the next corner.

Based on my experience, I can't recommend this hotel and I won't be staying there again.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
This was mine and my husband's first trip to France. Our first experience in this beautiful city was with Steeve at the front desk. We had so many questions and he was so kind and patient and knowledgeable.
The hotel is immaculate and plenty of space in the rooms.
Michael at the buffet is absolutely lovely.
Each staff member we encountered was extremely polite and patient !!! I wish every stay was as wonderful as this one!
Thank you Staff! You made our trip even more enjoyable and special !!!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The staff at this hotel are fantastic and very helpful, the location is good with lots of restaurants and shops near by, very safe hotel with great sercurity, rooms are small but okay for a short stay, We would stay here again thanks to the great staff.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Close to the metro! Stayed for 3 nights, room was small, but this is Paris! Lots of restaurants nearby. In front of a pharmacy if you wanna shop for some french beauty products! Staff was also friendly and very nice to guests!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Writing this on last night of a short stay at this hotel.

Complained to front desk staff this morning about clogged sink and shower stall. She answered with a totally sullen look as if I was stupid - quote with rolling eyes: yeah, this happens - and asked if I had lifted up the sink/drain hole cover. Franly was shocked why a trained hotel service staff would ask a guest to pry open up their own drain hole cover to fix a flooded shower! She then scribbled my room number on the piece of paper next to her.

Came back to my room this evening hoping that something would have been done but it was obvious that no one had even come to look at it. Just emerged from the shower after standing in 2 inches of water all the way trying to be extra careful not to cause a mini flood in the bathroom <sigh>.....have to be convinced there are far better 4* options than this in Paris.

Oh the plus side, the beds are comfy and the night desk manager is a polite chap in contrast to the recep staff in the morning.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I stayed in room 101 and i cant complain. Perfect location. Alot of shops around and very very secure with police around. I just want to give a BIG BIG thanks to Tricia for your excellent customer service and all the advise and assisting us with our Trip to Disneyland and Hopon Hopoff Bus tours tickets. You made out stay even more memorable. Keep it up will see you next year DEFINETLY. Regards Mr and Mrs Bouw from South Africa

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I have visited the Holiday Inn Elysees many times before. this my to go hotel when making a quick weekend getaway, great price, good rooms, friendly staff, and near all the best places in central Paris. I always feel welcome when visiting this hotel

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Stayed 4 days over the Easter break, fab location metro links on your door step easy to get around to see all the sites. Breakfast was great plenty of variety choose from yogurts, cereal, cooked breakfast and pastries very filling to start the day. Rooms very spacious we had connecting rooms for the kids. I would recommend and stay again. Staff friendly and helpful

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I have to say one of the most friendly hotels I have ever stayed in. Every single member of staff I had dealings with from consierge to cleaners was just lovely - so friendly and smiling! The waiter at breakfast deserves a special shout out for helping to serve me even though it was self serve! The room was a bit below average. Clean with all I neeed but not especially comfortable and very basic. But I slept well and the location was very central ideal to get to meetings. Food at breakfast was also good so I would stay again - but I cant award extremely highly as the room was quite poor

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Very good hotel and in a handy spot. The staff are excellent and take interest in giving personal attention to helping you. From advice on sight seeing to helping out the baby at breakfast.
Very enjoyable stay very clean and attentive staff

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Used my IHG points for 2 nights here. And i liked it. The check in - dont remember her name but she had a Congolese background - was the most perfect check in ever.
Room ok. Ground floor with a tiny window facing the street from where i could hear the chatting from people walking by. (I liked that also). Big bathroom. Good water pressure in shower. Brilliant staff.
Definitively a hotel to return to.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I enjoyed my stay at this hotel with my friends. The staff Tricia and Steeve were very helpful. They helped us get around Paris and the were very polite and friendly. I would recommend this hotel in Main for anyone looking for a friendly place to stay.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The Best Western moved us to this hotel. Location was nice, not too far from Macron residence. Room and bathroom were small, typical Paris. But king size bed was just what we wanted. Breakfast was ok but no decaf brewed coffee. Front desk service was helpful. Easy uber ride to Gare St. Lazare, our destination.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Great stay really nice hotel. Room is clean and has everything you need. Easy to reach the main touristic areas in Paris. The hotel is close to the Miromenil metro station.

Nice bar and breakfast has a good choice with food refilled regularly.

The reception staff are so helpful and very polite, a special thanks goes to Emanuel, who speaks excellent spanish. Would definitely recommend this hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Came for short holidays couple of months ago to enjoy my little break from work, so i decided to book your hotel according to my primary needs whenever i travel. Hotel well located by 8 minutes walk to the champs elysees and 3 minutes to the closest metro stop; the room was clean and the bed very comfortable which is very important for me. Being hosted by your positive and gorgeous staff complete my good experience with you especially with one of your staff member called Emanuel that was very helpful with his parisians trip advices around the area.
Surely will be a positive recommendation to my future traveller friends.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
My husband and I stayed at the Holiday Inn Paris Elysees for a week on our honeymoon. The hotel was well located and we could easily walk to the Metro (less than 2 minute walk!) and to attractions like the Champs Elysees and Louvre an easy walk away. The Eiffel tower was a short taxi ride approx 10-15 euros.

The room was well appointed but small (as are most hotel rooms in Paris) but the staff were so friendly and helpful. All staff spoke excellent English and it was nice when they remembered our names at breakfast or said hello when we were arriving or leaving the hotel each day. We really enjoyed our stay.

We enjoyed the hotel breakfast which was very French with lots of cold meat cuts, cheese, croissants/pastries and yogurts - it was hard to drag my husband away from the food... there are also lots of great restaurants nearby and a grocery shop around the corner which would be good for families.

We highly recommend the Holiday Inn Paris Elyees

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Having never been to Paris, we picked this hotel based on our having enough points to get a free night. We were pleasantly surprised. Centrally located within walking distance (15 minutes) of the Champs Elysees and 1 block from the Miromesnil Metro stop. Easy access to major sites and museums. Rooms were small but very nice and we didnt spend a lot of time in the room anyway. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Plenty of restaurants within walking distance. The only negative was it is right on the street so there was a lot of traffic noise, even at night.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: As a Gold Ihg rewards member , I have always been happy with the recognition when you check in with the Ihg group. Always experienced good service. Going for my 20th night with the group this year. Everyone in this hotel gave good service. Michael serving breakfast gave very good service. However on our first night, the guy at the reception was rude. When I requested for a shaving kit , he said you come down here and get it. When I requested for extra pillow, he said you have it in your cabinet. I called back and said there is no pillow. He was unfriendly on the phone and said he will check if he can find one!!!. I have to follow up and tell him to cancel the extra pillow as we are going to sleep already . Then he goes up and knocks at our door and gives us a pillow with an angry voice. Im alone in this hotel!! Definitely not staying in this holiday inn again . This is not holiday inn standard. No right to carry the holiday inn name.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Recently, my mother and I stayed here for a few days while coming back from a trip to Te Aviv. Even though the room was a bit small and closet/drawer space was limited, both she and I were exceedingly impressed with the exemplary hospitality of the staff, particularly Steve. Steve and the others went out of their way to advise and suggest tours, sights, restaurants, etc. They helped me navigate the Metro system and treated my mother's concerns (which were not a lot) with graciousness and genuinely friendly smiles. Kudos to all of them, especially Steve (who should get a raise--take note Holiday Inn management).

The location was great--the Metro is just a block away and the Champs-Elysees is nearby. And breakfast was wonderful--lots of goodies.

If you're going to be in Paris for a few days, I'd highly recommend this hotel. You'll be very pleased.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Stayed here for 3 nights with my sister, the hotel was very nice.
Room was not ready when we arrived at lunchtime so we stored our luggage and went out for the day.
the hotel is like a boutique hotel in the lobby, very nice public toilets.

The rooms are small but do the hob, we had a lovey bathroom, there is a kettle, and tv. We had to call for an ironing board brought to the the room but this was done very quickly.
Food was a little limited so we ate out.
Very close to the local transportation also, Miromesnil is a station on lines 9 and 13 of the Paris Mtro is literally a 2 minute walk from the hotel so very handy.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Every thing was amazing
I highly recommend the place the place located in a central location. Comfortable, clean and the staff are wonderful.
We stayed in the excellent room in the fifth floor. Pleasant and quiet.
Breakfast is rich fresh and tasty.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: One of the better Holiday Inn properties that I have stayed in. Lobby is inviting and staff is helpful, courteous, and charming. Room well appointed, and the bathroom was excellent with a large shower. Great location within the city, easy walking to many places or the train for points further away. Desk staff gave excellent and detailed directions for navigating the train. Highly recommend!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
The hotel is great, the design is modern. The Room are comfortable and clean . The Breakfast was generous and tasty .
A great deal to combine leisure and business while being close to the heart of Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We had a quick trip to Paris and this hotel was in a perfect spot! The breakfast was outstanding and Christopher was the host of a lifetime.

We had the family room (1 K, 2 Single Adjoining Rooms) and it was clean and reasonably priced.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Great location for the train and bike share. Nice restaurants and supermarket nearby. Staff friendly and helpful. Rooms nice albeit a bit small by Australian standards. Breakfast was basic but complimentary.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The hotel was so easy to find, it is just a block away from the Metro. The breakfast selection was very filling as well - a lot of yummy choices. The staff were very helpful - a very special mention to Steeve Bazot - he was phenomenal! He helped us with our tour plans around the city.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Booked a one night stay at Holiday Inn Elyses based on it being a decent hotel from a previous stay and it being close to my companys office in Paris and my usual hotels being fully booked.

This time, I booked a Queen room on a room only basis but as a Spire Elite was upgraded to a King Exec room.

The room (505) seemed much more spacious than the room in my last stay. The bathroom was large with a large walk in shower and the toiletries seem to have improved in quality (branded C.O. Bigelow).

The fan in the bathroom wouldnt turn off and the traffic outside was fairly noisy so I wore ear plugs to sleep.

WiFi was reasonably quick. A complimentary bottle of water and a Twix provided.

I didnt try breakfast and at 18 I wouldnt as there are many good bakeries etc in the area.

Would I return? Perhaps. But I will try to book my usual hotels first.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
With 6 journeys in Paris and almost 2 full months stay in this hotel I can only feedback like this: Excellence!
Comfort and lovable staff! Among the sweetest staff: Steeve, Araci, Emanuel. I just say sorry for not knowing all the names, but no exception done in making me feel part of their "family". Thank you all so so much!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The Holiday Inn Paris Elysees was a great pick. This was a family trip that included my wife and teenage daughter. We stayed one of the larger rooms and found it perfect with a king bed and a pull out couch. The room was a welcomed relief after hearing about the small rooms generally throughout Europe. Access to metro, shops, and restaurants was acceptable. The staff was fantastic; especially the front desk who helped us navigate a new and unfamiliar city. Would we return to this hotel..absolutely!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
I was in this hotel in March. when I chose the hotel I immediately became interested in this Hotel. I liked the price and the place.
I like it. in this hotel, clean and comfortable rooms. good breakfast. very convenient location.
nice place and friendly staff, I recommend!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
Holiday Inn Elysees is the ideal hotel destination for an easy, central Paris hotel, I have been to this property several times and the staff has always been very kind to me and my partner, Araci, Steve and Emanuele were an absolute pleasure the last time we visited Paris, they are so friendly. I will continue to visit Paris and stay in the same Hotel.

The hotel has also done a great job updating Bed, Lobby Decor and security, I highly recommend this hotel, great prices , great location, the breakfast is also very well done.

Its like a boutique hotel in the centre of Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I travel to Paris monthly and could stay many places and I choose Holiday Inn Elysees primarily for the staff! Steeve Bazot is always there with a smile, great conversation and a perfect restaurant pick. He has even walked me to the restaurant so I wont get lost! Araci is so sweet. I had to change rooms in the middle of my stay and when I got back to the hotel after a LONG day she had my new room ready and moved everything from my old room ( with permission of course) and put everything exactly in place . All of the staff is the same ! Nice and welcoming!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This was one of the best city hotels I have stayed in for a very long time. The location absolutely perfect. Our family room which consisted of 2 rooms interconnecting were clean & comfortable and although I wouldn't call them spacious there was plenty of room for what we all needed. I would definitely go back.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I am travelling for business on almost weekly basis but last week for the first time ever I left my mobile in the cab that brought me to the Holiday Inn Elysee in Paris. Due to the hectic traffic situation during peak hours, the taxi was already gone. Coming to the reception, the Holiday Inn Front end officer on duty around 18:30 managed to track the taxi (out of probably thousands in Paris) and 25 Minutes later I had my phone back even delivered at the reception. This only with a small receipt I could give not even having a telephone nr. In 20 years of international business travel this was one of the most professional hotel staff interventions I've ever seen. Top job & Top hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
The hotel is perfect for a business trip.
Great location, lot of shops, high standards service and a lovely team. Peace and quiet room. Wi-fi is finally working in a hotel!
I highly recommend this place.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Stayed in this hotel whilst I was in the city on business, the hotel is not in a touristy location but great for business trips. It's modern, very clean and comfortable, breakfast was good as was the coffee. I would recommend this hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: We booked a room very last minute when our prior arrangements fell through. Steeve at the Holiday Inn Paris Elysees was so very helpful in getting us settled. The hotel is comfortable and their breakfast was very nice. The location is very convenient to sites, great restaurants and metro stops.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
People, people, people & location who made it worth staying here its unfair to qualify for a 4 stars hotel with such a very limited facility!
Otherwise I would rate it 4 or 5 if it was a 3 stars hotel.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Very awesome place have a grt fun lovely to see and visit all around a new experience of my life with my family and friends to enjoy and work there is a refreshing nature my mind is fresh now and ready to work

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: What a great boutique hotel situated in the heart of Paris . Located near some pretty cool museums which are all in walking distance , as long as you have good shoes for doing so. Within walking distance of the Eiffel Tower l'arc de triomphe . Grand and petit palais . Presidential palace and the embassies of GB and the USA . Neat little store for beer wine and some snacks at night . U won't regret this place . Breakfast included and much better than some breakfasts I have had in my trips

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This hotel is simply amazing and great location (right next to Champs d'Elysees). It's clean and tidy, the staff (particularly Steeve and Arand) are so welcoming and accommodating. My boyfriend and I had booked a terrible hotel across the street, and we were welcomed with open arms to the Holiday Inn in our times of despair. We could not have asked for a better stay!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We enjoyed our 6 nights stay at Holiday Inn lyse. The reception team were very warm and welcoming upon check-in. Staff always had a smile on their face and were available for recommendations and directions.

We opted for the executive room for the duration of our stay. By North American standards, the room was still on the small side, however, the room was clean and equipped with adequate storage and comfortable king size bed.

The hotel is conveniently located with nearby metro and multiple cafes. Our favourite was Eric Kayser which is just around the corner from the hotel. Croissant and cappuccino will cost approx 6 euro. Distance to Champs Elysses from hotel is about 10 minutes, and approximately 20 mins to Arc de Triumph. Monoprix, the "must do" supermarket carries a great selection of food and treats is 10 mins away.

Overall, we enjoyed our stay and would recommend this hotel to our friends.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
It was a double room but there was not enough space for two of us to move around at the same time. We had to take turns to sit on the bed or move around. This has got to be the tiniest room I've ever experienced in Europe.
Another annoyance was the paper cups provided for tea/coffee.
Great location and fab staff but the lack of space and cost is ridiculous.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We've booked a family room for two adults and two children. Got two adjacent interconnected rooms which appeared to be very convenient. The staff was very friendly and helpful all along the stay. The real benefit is the location - one block from the metro, walking distance (10 minutes) from Champs Elysee and other nice places, plenty of food options on the same block.
We've experienced some maintenance problems during our stay (a burned-out electricity socket, leaking shower, window shades which do not close completely) - all are minor, but they make a difference between "very good" and "excellent".

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: I stayed in this hotel with my family and the experience was good. The location of the hotel is very good, 1 minute walking from the metro station and 10 minuted walking from the Champs Elysees Street. The front desk staff are very friendly, knowledgeable and they offer a great advice about the tours and sightseeing in Paris. The lobby had candy jars that my kids just loved and there was a computer and printer open for all guests. The rooms are a little small but for me that is expected in Paris hotels. This hotel will be one of my choices when I travel to Paris again.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
I stayed there for 4 nights on August 2017 with my wife,and the stay was just perfect
Staff are friendly and supportive specially the people on the reception, location is great, breakfast is good- not much option. I would stay again in this hotel

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
We initially booked two interconnecting rooms, which was advertised as two rooms adjacent to each other. On arrival, we learned that this was actually four rooms, on separate floors. With four children with ages ranging from an infant to a six year old, it is unacceptable to have preschool age children to sleep in alone in a hotel room, yet this was what the management expected.

Upon learning this, I called IHG customer service in the USA who called the management in Paris to fix this, however the management refused to accommodate us and still charged us for four rooms for three adults and four children. Again, even if three adults stayed in a separate room with one child, that would still leave one child, under six years of age to sleep by himself in his own room, in a foreign country in which he does not speak the native vernacular.

Without any choice, we stayed at the hotel with four rooms. We spoke to the night manager who agreed with our situation and agreed to refund us one room for one night. This room that we gave up was rented out the next night. Upon check out, the management refused to credit us one night in this room #206 although we did not have access to this room as it was rented out to another party.

We tried to resolve this issue, however the arrogant management at the Holiday Inn in Paris refused to discuss this further. Email messages sent to IHG management in the USA went unheard as they recommended that I contact the Holiday Inn in Paris.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
A quaint hotel with comfortable airy rooms (though in room lighting needs to be slightly stronger especially if u want to use make up & which you will want to when holidaying in Paris after all!);extremely helpful concierge! The hotel does not have any food facilities but with over 30 cafes within 5 mins walking distance that wasn't a problem at all... If u like to walk it's about 20/25 minutes trot to Arc de Triumph, Louvre, Eiffel - need I say more about the location.
Winding stairways inside the hotel is lovely!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: This hotel is not the Taj. It is a boutique style venue that offers amazing customer service. Our first trip to Paris was highlighted by the connections made with both Steeve and Alexandra. Holiday Inn should be very proud of both of them, they were better than private tour guides! The time and energy they both offered to ensure our trip was memorable exceeded experiences I've had in exclusive resorts.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: We stayed here for 3 nights in between Venice and London. The hotel was centrally located to lots of nice restaurants and transportation to get around the city. We were a block away from the metro. We came in earlier than our check in but were able to use the facilities to clean ourselves and change our clothing from a long overnight train ride from Venice. The hotel staff were so nice. Always willing to help us,give us directions, and also advice on restaurants. The candy dishes were a hit with my family. My husband and children ate candy every single time we were in the lobby. They definitely miss the candy! The rooms were very spacious and very,very clean! We are Spire members and were given a connecting family room on the 4th florr. The bathroom was huge. Walk in shower,plenty of counter space,and a heated towel rack. The room is equipped with an electric tea kettle with teas and coffees. There were also some biscuits(cookies) with the tea. I would definitely recommend this hotel and will stay here on our next trip to Paris

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Love the corner whereby they prepared complimentary breakfast and tea . You can sip some tea or coffee with this beautiful tea cup together with some French Pastries. You can also find lollipops and jelly beans at the lobby which makes you scream with delight like a child. Service was good and the stay at this hotel was comfortable. Location is convenient with cafes , bistro & supermarket nearby Will not hesitate to recommend to other Travellers .

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Great location, quality of location, tight rooms, but you shouldn't be stuck in your room while in Paris. Icing on the cake: Steve and Jeff were absolutely great hosts and conversationalists that made our coming/going and winding downs a pleasure. Seize soixante-quatre!

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: Hotel is in such a great location, the staff were brilliant and so helpful with everything, Clean, efficient and the breakfasts were superb. Highly recommended and we enjoyed having an adjoining room as requested.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews: The hotel was conveniently located and very comfortable. The staff were diligent and very knowledgeable with 24 hour coverage. The bed was very comfortable and air conditioning quiet. It was a good hotel and we would stay there next time.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
My Fianc and I came here to Paris for our first visit and since we are both Travel Agents and members with IHG, we booked the Holiday Inn Paris Elysees for its location. What we got was so much more. From the moment we arrived we were greeted with smiles and were coming off of a 14 hour flight and arrived at around 10 pm.
Our room was waiting for us and it was a very comfortable Room with an amazing King bed. The room was super clean and the bathroom just marvelous.

Every morning of our 4 day stay here, we were greeted in the morning and afternoon by Steeve, Jean-Francois, Emilie, Michael, and Giulia. They were so kind, attended to all of our needs(and we were very needy since it was our first time in Paris. Really need to thank Steeve as he was always ready and willing to recommend a local place for us to eat or get a Baguette in the morning. Every time we needed anything , from a cab to getting extra pillows
Steeve was so attentive and the team delivered every time. We liked this hotel so much that after leaving the city for a few days to explore the country side, we returned and booked another night at the Elysees and loved it and Emilie and Steeve were ready, smiling and went above and beyond our expectations

We will always recommend and stay here when we visit Paris in the future.

hotel: Holiday Inn Paris - Elysees, an IHG hotel
reviews:
First of all the good stuff:

- clean rooms
- fantastic location. You really cannot get better at this price range
- amazing staff - the reception staff (Stevee (?) in particular) are welcoming and helpful.
I loved the cute sweets and nice touches that demonstrate that the team really care about the hotel

Minus points
- I came back to a flood in my room. Not a massive issue as they promptly moved me but a hassle nonetheless
- there was no hot water coming through my shower in the morning. I am not a morning person at the best of times and a cold water shower didn't make me feel that brilliant!
- most of the time there was only one person on reception which meant that everything - bar service, check in, booking queries, room issues etc had to go through that one person. It meant that some things took longer than they should.

I have thought hard about whether to award three or four blobs to this hotel and have finally settled on three because that wouldn't be fair on how I typically mark on TA. Having said that, please do not be put off. I would definitely come back here and see if I was just unlucky with my stay this time.
